Public Enterprises Minister Pravin Gordhan and Public Protector Busisiwe Mkhwebane are set to face off in court on Tuesday. JOHANNESBURG - Public Enterprises Minister Pravin Gordhan and Public Protector Busisiwe Mkhwebane will go head to head in court on Tuesday. The pair will face-off over Mkhwebane's report on the so-called SARS rogue unit. LIVESTREAM: Gordhan, Mkhwebane face-off in court Earlier in July, Gordhan instructed his legal team to prepare an urgent review of the report. 